title: Parkland's Ben Jago is lehighvalleylive Boys Soccer Player of the Week
text:
Ben Jago , Parkland 
The senior midfielder stepped up in the Eastern Pennsylvania Conference tournament as the Trojans were left to play without their leading scorer, Tyler Madeira, due to injury. 
Jago scored a goal in each of Parkland’s EPC victories over Freedom, Emmaus and Pocono Mountain East. He also had an assist in the Trojans' narrow 4-3 win over the Patriots. 
It’s easily the most productive six-day span of Jago’s season. 
Honorable mention : Jr. DEF Jonathan Blaine , Northwestern Lehigh; Sr. FWD JD Haaf , Northwestern Lehigh; Sr. MID Keegan Halloran , Phillipsburg; Jr. FWD Peter Kwakye-Ackah , Parkland; Sr. FWD Brett Nesfeder , Notre Dame; So. Kevin Siebens , North Warren.
